         <div>
            <head>1.4.1885 Mittwoch</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49025">Berlin</placeName>. April 1. 1885.</p>
            <p>This morning the first thing we did was again to go to the Wilhelm Strasse where we
               saw a huge pyramid of fruit and flowers and vegetables being carried in to <persName key="8568">Bismarcks</persName> on a stretcher. Afterwards went to see the
               beginning of the <placeName key="58049">Reichstags building</placeName>. Not much to
               be seen, as it is hardly begun. From there we went to the <orgName key="x">Hotel de
                  Russie</orgName> or some such name near the Spree and had breakfast. From there to
               the Rathaus. Very fine and worth seeing. After that
                  <persName key="856">aunt Lulu</persName> went to the <orgName key="66875">National
                  Gallery</orgName> and I to the <orgName key="68127">Museum</orgName>
               <note type="reg">Altes und Neues Museum</note>. Was very tired so that I could hardly
               enjoy it. Saw the really <hi rend="ul">magnificent</hi> picture of Holzschuher<note type="reg">
                  <name type="work" key="28830">Bildnis des Hieronymus Holzschuher</name>
               </note> by <persName key="5214">Dürer</persName>. I have never in my life seen
               anything so lifelike. He looks as if he was going to come out of his frame, without
               any exageration. Afterwards spent a good deal of time looking at the sculptures of
                  Pergamum<note type="reg">
                  <name type="work" key="59415">Pergamonaltar
                     (Berlin)</name>
               </note> which are also splendid; I could hardly enjoy them
               though properly today as I was so dead tired. Had to go away at five as the <orgName key="68127">museum</orgName> shuts then. Went to Table d&#x2019;Hôte at the Hotel. After that to the <orgName key="x">Deutsche
                  Theather</orgName>, where we saw <name type="work" key="28831">Prinz Friedrich von
                  Homburg</name>
               <note type="reg">
                  <persName key="8388">Kleist</persName>
               </note>. Not very interesting.</p>
         </div>
